ement l√† o√π il s‚Äô√©tait arr√™t√©.\\r\\n\\r\\nNous explorerons ces nouveaut√©s avec des d√©mos en direct, des avant/apr√®s bluffants et des conseils concrets pour tirer parti de chaque am√©lioration. Venez voir comment .NET 10 transforme Blazor‚Ä¶ et pourquoi vous ne voudrez plus revenir en arri√®re.\",\r\n      \"startsAt\": \"2025-11-13T11:40:00\",\r\n      \"endsAt\": \"2025-11-13T12:25:00\",\r\n      \"isServiceSession\": false,\r\n      \"isPlenumSession\": false,\r\n      \"speakers\": [\r\n        \"7abba503-072d-4023-97d0-3b98e2a220ad\",\r\n        \"58b7e053-0d87-4bbc-a0c5-fb03e0b34166\"\r\n      ],\r\n      \"categoryItems\": [\r\n        373900,\r\n        373902,\r\n        373919,\r\n        373923\r\n      ],\r\n      \"questionAnswers\": [],\r\n      \"roomId\": 67254,\r\n      \"liveUrl\": null,\r\n      \"recordingUrl\": null,\r\n      \"status\": \"Accepted\",\r\n      \"isInformed\": true,\r\n      \"isConfirmed\": true\r\n    },\r\n    {\r\n      \"id\": \"976961\",\r\n      \"title\": \"Failure MUST be an option\",\r\n      \"description\": \"The point of this talk is to demystify failure. To stop making it a shameful taboo, which we hide as much as possible, which no one wants to talk about, when there is so much to learn from it.\\r\\n\\r\\nVery inspired by the work of Amy Edmondson, I address what she describes as the \\\"spectrum\\\" of failures, which ranges from reprehensible failures to those that should be encouraged.\\r\\n\\r\\nFailure being emotionally charged, the challenge is to make people and organizations understand that, in many cases, it is appropriate to detach ourselves from it to concentrate on the lessons learned from it: adapting a failing process, adjust a method, strengthen and propagate a practice that works well...\\r\\n\\r\\nRich in anecdotes and parallels with everyday life, this talk is a call for humility in front of failure, the unpredictable, uncertainty, but also a great way to spread the idea that we learn a lot by making mistakes.\",\r\n      \"startsAt\": \"2025-11-13T11:40:00\",\r\n      \"endsAt\": \"2025-11-13T12:25:00\",\r\n      \"isServiceSession\": false,\r\n      \"isPlenumSession\": false,\r\n      \"speakers\": [\r\n        \"521e874f-9374-4e61-8e22-a038333f8202\"\r\n      ],\r\n      \"categoryItems\": [\r\n        373900,\r\n        373917,\r\n        373918,\r\n        373922\r\n      ],\r\n      \"questionAnswers\": [],\r\n      \"roomId\": 67255,\r\n      \"liveUrl\": null,\r\n      \"recordingUrl\": null,\r\n      \"status\": \"Accepted\",\r\n      \"isInformed\": true,\r\n      \"isConfirmed\": true\r\n    },\r\n    {\r\n      \"id\": \"982048\",\r\n      \"title\": \"The art of Mona, from building to deploying with Ninjas\",\r\n      \"description\": \"Agentic DevOps : Create, maintain, deploy , monitor, enhance all your DevOps cycle with GitHub agents.\",\r\n      \"startsAt\": \"2025-11-13T11:40:00\",\r\n      \"endsAt\": \"2025-11-13T12:25:00\",\r\n      \"isServiceSession\": false,\r\n      \"isPlenumSession\": false,\r\n      \"speakers\": [\r\n        \"0e1a5984-7896-44d0-a3b9-bcfdc0731063\"\r\n      ],\r\n      \"categoryItems\": [\r\n        373900,\r\n        373916,\r\n        373919,\r\n        373922\r\n      ],\r\n      \"questionAnswers\": [],\r\n      \"roomId\": 67257,\r\n      \"liveUrl\": null,\r\n      \"recordingUrl\": null,\r\n      \"status\": \"Accepted\",\r\n      \"isInformed\": true,\r\n      \"isConfirmed\": true\r\n    },\r\n    {\r\n      \"id\": \"1046389\",\r\n      \"title\": \"IA et biais sexistes : comprendre, mesurer, corriger\",\r\n      \"description\": \"L‚Äôintelligence artificielle est partout : elle trie des candidatures, recommande des contenus, aide √† poser des diagnostics‚Ä¶ Mais derri√®re cette apparente neutralit√©, elle peut aussi reproduire et amplifier des biais, notamment des biais sexistes, pr√©sents dans les donn√©es d‚Äôentra√Ænement.\\r\\nCe talk propose de d√©mystifier ces biais : comment ils se forment, quels sont leurs impacts, et surtout comment les outils techniques comme Fairlearn permettent de les identifier et les att√©nuer. On parlera de m√©triques d‚Äô√©quit√©, de visualisations interactives, et de m√©thodes simples pour rendre les mod√®les plus justes.\\r\\nParce que l‚ÄôIA n‚Äôest pas une bo√Æte noire magique, mais un reflet de nos choix, il est essentiel de la construire avec conscience, responsabilit√© et exigence.\",\r\n      \"startsAt\": \"2025-11-13T12:00:00\",\r\n      \"endsAt\": \"2025-11-13T12:15:00\",\r\n      \"isServiceSession\": false,\r\n      \"isPlenumSession\": false,\r\n      \"speakers\": [\r\n        \"35ac7222-c7ed-40a3-960b-44223768ae4b\"\r\n      ],\r\n      \"categoryItems\": [\r\n        373899,\r\n        373916,\r\n        373918,\r\n        373923\r\n      ],\r\n      \"questionAnswers\": [],\r\n      \"roomId\": 67258,\r\n      \"liveUrl\": null,\r\n      \"recordingUrl\": null,\r\n      \"status\": \"Accepted\",\r\n      \"isInformed\": true,\r\n      \"isConfirmed\": true\r\n    },\r\n    {\r\n      \"id\": \"1051080\",\r\n      \"title\": \"AI4Fun\",\r\n      \"description\": \"L'IA s'applique aujourd'hui dans tellement de domaines, qu'en est-il du Fun ? Avec mes comp√®res David Rousset et S√©bastien Pertus nous vous proposons de nous retrouver pour une session divertissante mais toujours technique ou l'IA et les agents seront au service du Fun et de la bonne humeur.\",\r\n      \"startsAt\": \"2025-11-13T13:30:00\",\r\n      \"endsAt\": \"2025-11-13T14:15:00\",\r\n      \"isServiceSession\": false,\r\n      \"isPlenumSession\": false,\r\n      \"speakers\": [\r\n        \"489b1a64-23f3-4c56-b528-86e5e68e6657\",\r\n        \"4490c811-c3d2-4022-96dc-d5e51959ec20\"\r\n      ],\r\n      \"categoryItems\": [\r\n        373900,\r\n        373916,\r\n        373919,\r\n        373923\r\n      ],\r\n      \"questionAnswers\": [],\r\n      \"roomId\": 67253,\r\n      \"liveUrl\": null,\r\n      \"recordingUrl\": null,\r\n      \"status\": \"Accepted\",\r\n      \"isInformed\": true,\r\n      \"isConfirmed\": false\r\n    },\r\n    {\r\n      \"id\": \"971770\",\r\n      \"title\": \"Using GenAI on and inside your code, what could possibly go wrong?\",\r\n      \"description\": \"With GenAI, developers are shifting from traditional code reuse to generating new code snippets by prompting GenAI, leading to a significant change in the ways software gets developed. \\r\\nSeveral academic studies show that AI generated code based on LLM's that are trained on vulnerable OSS implementations lead to vulnerable generated code. Another study showed that developers tend to trust GenAI created code more than human created code. Combining that with the higher code velocity it will result in more vulnerabilities in it's output. \\r\\nUsing an AI system that runs an LLM also has additional risks tied to it, related to jailbreaks, data poisoning and malicious agents, recursive learning and IP infringements. \\r\\nIn this presentation, we will examine real-world data from several academic studies to understand how GenAI is changing software security, the risks it introduces, and possible strategies to address these emerging issues.\",\r\n      \"startsAt\": \"2025-11-13T13:30:00\",\r\n      \"endsAt\": \"2025-11-13T14:15:00\",\r\n      \"isServiceSession\": false,\r\n      \"isPlenumSession\": false,\r\n      \"speakers\": [\r\n        \"d07b21cb-12c3-467f-aaf8-211891376cc9\"\r\n      ],\r\n      \"categoryItems\": [\r\n        373900,\r\n        373913,\r\n        373919,\r\n        373922\r\n      ],\r\n      \"questionAnswers\": [],\r\n      \"roomId\": 67254,\r\n      \"liveUrl\": null,\r\n      \"recordingUrl\": null,\r\n      \"status\": \"Accepted\",\r\n      \"isInformed\": true,\r\n      \"isConfirmed\": true\r\n    },\r\n    {\r\n      \"id\": \"971472\",\r\n      \"title\": \"Optimize your event-driven architectures with Drasi\",\r\n      \"description\": \"Event-driven architectures have become a staple of modern microservices, but they often remain surprisingly static‚Äîhardcoded triggers, rigid flows, and limited adaptability. Enter Drasi, a cloud-native workflow engine that embraces change as a first-class citizen.\\r\\n\\r\\nIn this talk, we‚Äôll explore how Drasi reimagines orchestration by shifting from traditional event-driven models to reactive, state-aware workflows. Built for Kubernetes and designed with microservices in mind, Drasi enables systems to respond dynamically to real-world changes‚Äîwhether it‚Äôs a new deployment, a failed job, or a shifting business rule.\\r\\n\\r\\nWe‚Äôll cover:\\r\\n\\r\\n- The limitations of static event-driven systems in cloud-native environments\\r\\n- How Drasi models workflows as state machines that evolve with your system\\r\\n- Native integrations with Kubernetes, Dapr, and KEDA\\r\\n- Real-world use cases where Drasi simplifies complexity and boosts resilience\\r\\n\\r\\nWhether you're building distributed systems, managing microservices, or just tired of brittle pipelines, this session will show you how Drasi brings orchestration to life‚Äîreactive, observable, and ready for change.\",\r\n      \"startsAt\": \"2025-11-13T13:30:00\",\r\n      \"endsAt\": \"2025-11-13T14:15:00\",\r\n      \"isServiceSession\": false,\r\n      \"isPlenumSession\": false,\r\n      \"speakers\": [\r\n        \"6bd79ef2-920e-47b2-97bd-2854d7769adc\"\r\n      ],\r\n      \"categoryItems\": [\r\n        373900,\r\n        373910,\r\n        373918,\r\n        373923\r\n      ],\r\n      \"questionAnswers\": [],\r\n      \"roomId\": 67255,\r\n      \"liveUrl\": null,\r\n      \"recordingUrl\": null,\r\n      \"status\": \"Accepted\",\r\n      \"isInformed\": true,\r\n      \"isConfirmed\": true\r\n    },\r\n    {\r\n      \"id\": \"969123\",\r\n      \"title\": \"The art of data retention in PostgreSQL\",\r\n      \"description\": \"As developers, we often focus on building fast and reliable applications, but growing datasets can silently degrade performance and complicate maintenance. In the spirit of the Bushido code, this talk embraces discipline and foresight to confront uncontrolled data growth in PostgreSQL with clarity and precision.\\r\\n\\r\\nWe'll explore practical techniques to keep databases lean and efficient. Topics include how declarative partitioning simplifies table management and speeds up queries, how native LZ4 compression reduces storage overhead on cold data, and how to offload outdated or rarely accessed information to external systems using Foreign Data Wrappers. The session will also cover the implementation of automated retention policies that help manage data lifecycles with minimal developer effort.\\r\\n\\r\\nThis talk is intended for developers and engineers looking to scale responsibly, maintain performance, and apply thoughtful craftsmanship to the long-term health of their PostgreSQL systems.\",\r\n      \"startsAt\": \"2025-11-13T13:30:00\",\r\n      \"endsAt\": \"2025-11-13T14:15:00\",\r\n      \"isServiceSession\": false,\r\n      \"isPlenumSession\": false,\r\n      \"speakers\": [\r\n        \"90c9fbbb-630c-4b34-88c0-3cb7c32ceae9\"\r\n      ],\r\n      \"categoryItems\": [\r\n        373900,\r\n        373914,\r\n        373919,\r\n        373922\r\n      ],\r\n      \"questionAnswers\": [],\r\n      \"roomId\": 67256,\r\n      \"liveUrl\": null,\r\n      \"recordingUrl\": null,\r\n      \"status\": \"Accepted\",\r\n      \"isInformed\": true,\r\n      \"isConfirmed\": true\r\n    },\r\n    {\r\n      \"id\": \"1014376\",\r\n      \"title\": \".NET Aspire et architecture micro-service √† l'aide de YARP comme reverse proxy.\",\r\n      \"description\": \".Net Aspire est un outil essentiel pour mettre √† disposition des d√©veloppeurs un environement applicatifs.\\r\\nLe but de la session est d'expliquer ce que .NET Aspire apporte et de montrer comment on peut cr√©er une architecture microservice avec de l'Open Telemetry et d'un API Gateway bas√© s